name: 11 - Verify Transaction Fee API call with different types of AMEX with PAYSAFE9909 processor

testSteps.description: Example #1: {NICN=AmexStandard, Amount=80.00, Region=Chargeable state, Processor=Paysafe9909, HttpStatusCode=201, TransactionFee=Interchange:FixedFee:GatewayMarkup:NetworkFee:SurchxPercentage, Sid=NotNull, Message=ok}

children.description:
When I call Transaction Fee API with the following data
| Merchant | NICN | Amount | Region | Processor |
| Coastline | AmexStandard | 80.00 | Chargeable state | Paysafe9909 |

Load transaction fee api request:       | Merchant  | NICN         | Amount | Region           | Processor   |
      | Coastline | AmexStandard | 80.00  | Chargeable state | Paysafe9909 |

Then Verify the response is as follows
| HttpStatusCode | TransactionFee | Sid | Message |
| 201 | Interchange:FixedFee:GatewayMarkup:NetworkFee:SurchxPercentage | NotNull | ok |

Load expected api response:       | HttpStatusCode | TransactionFee                                                 | Sid     | Message |
      | 201            | Interchange:FixedFee:GatewayMarkup:NetworkFee:SurchxPercentage | NotNull | ok      |

testSteps.description: Example #2: {NICN=AmexStandard, Amount=80.00, Region=Non-Chargeable state, Processor=Paysafe9909, HttpStatusCode=201, TransactionFee=0.00, Sid=NotNull, Message=ok}
